HEADWORD: gopherwood
<hw>gopherwood</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A small handsome round-headed
deciduous tree (<spn>Cladrastis lutea</spn>) having showy white flowers
in terminal clusters and heavy hardwood yielding yellow dye; also called
<altname>yellowwood</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Kentucky yellowwood, <spn>Cladrastis lutea</spn>,
Cladrastis kentukea, yellowwood.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Goracco</ent>⟦br⟧
